Peel, core, and thinly slice apples. Melt butter in medium skillet over medium heat. Add apples; cook 3 to 4 minutes or until tender crisp. Set aside. Tear croissants into 2-inch pieces. Toss with reserved apples in a 9-inch square baking dish. Whisk eggs, yolks, sugar, vanilla and peel together in medium bowl; add cream and milk; mix well. Pour mixture over croissants; refrigerate for one hour or overnight. Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Place pan in shallow hot water bath, cover with foil. Bake 45 minutes. Remove foil; continue to bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes or until center is set and top is golden.